social_posts.post_text: Happy Monday!!! Making this week a splash!!!

Luke’s 1st and last day…😢 
This week has been a little emotional for me as we say goodbye to Kamiloiki Elementary school. No more arts and crafts and school performances.

1st DegreeBlack Belt!!!

Brock’s journey has been a long one. He struggled focusing as a child, wasn’t the most coordinated and he wanted to quit so many times. He started when he was 5 years old. 10 years later he earned his Black Belt recommendation and yesterday, at 16 years old he earned his 1st degree! I could not be more proud. 

We are so incredibly lucky to learn from Grandmaster He Ill Cho, one of the world’s most decorated Taekwondo Masters. He has never given up on Brock and he has always said what you need to hear not what you want to hear. We are blessed to have an incredible influence and leader like Grandmaster in our lives. I know once day his words and lessons will resonate with them in real life.

Now Luke is right behind Brock, just a few tests away from his black belt.

If you are looking for something that builds character and confidence with your children (and adults), put them in martial arts! It’s not about teaching your children to fight or learn self defense. This is a life lesson that teaches discipline, follow through, respect, self control and so much more! 

@brockhawaii @brock_does_kicks @students.of.gm.cho
